<br>
With 15 classes it seems difficult to give every single one some &quot;class defining&quot; ability that makes them wanted for raids. <br>
<br>
I think verant looks at a bigger picture when they balance the classes. How good are you on a raid, in a group, and solo? Some classes are more geared towards groups than soloing and vice versa (guess which one we are!). <br>
<br>
What is a paladin's usefulness on a raid? Shadownight? Necro? Druid? Mages? Now well can these guys solo (sorry pally's)? <br>
<br>
Compare their &quot;class defining spells&quot;  FOR RAIDS to ours? Lay on hands, Harm Touch, Feign Death (almost always see monks used instead), Mana Dump, Summon Corpse, PotG, Mod Rods, Call of the Hero. <br>
<br>
I think you can SP and savagery to that list and it wouldn't seem out of place. Most of the ones up there are VERY situational and others can only affect a single target. <br>
<br>
Now look at the opposites. Enchanters, Clerics, Rogues, Monks, Warriors. You get KEI, Complete Heal, Rezz, highest DPS, and best tanking ability. Now how well do these guys solo?  And yes I know they CAN solo but if you take an EQUALLY skilled player and let them at both classes (one of these vs a beastlord) I bet the beastlord is outright better.<br>
<br>
Sorry guys, I really enjoy my class even though I admit there are far better classes on raids. That is how beastlords were intended to be. You would think that is obvious to someone starting a new character since it is a pet class.  <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=306527>Kaboll Guy - 56 Beast Lord (Prexus)</a><br>
